// Pre-built Barry book — seeded automatically on first login
const BARRY_BOOK = {"setupDone":true,"title":"Barry is Terrific","authorName":"Debi Black Vandiver","trimSize":"8x10","fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","pages":[{"id":"7f269cfb-4d85-4c0a-b373-a47b64785ceb","layoutId":"title-page","text":"Barry is Terrific\n\nA Wilderwhim Story\n\nBy Debi Black Vandiver","fontSize":38,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"center","textZone":{"x":10,"y":30,"w":80,"h":40},"images":[],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":true},{"id":"06c47e23-c7be-423c-99b7-b38166a36120","layoutId":"text-only","text":"Copyright 2024 Debi Black Vandiver\nAll rights reserved.","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"center","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":84},"images":[],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"b546cfaf-daa7-47dd-9fbc-64aec10cb92f","layoutId":"text-only","text":"For the dreamer in me\nand the dreamer in You\u2026","fontSize":30,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"center","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":84},"images":[],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"8c1ea2b4-fe3b-446e-b19a-54f8b3b5df77","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"only bears could understand, his fishing hat tipped low, his paws tucked in just right, and beside him sat a picnic basket; half open, as if it had given up its secrets.\n\nInside were the very best kind of things. Peanut butter and jelly sandwiches and a bottle of lemonade, still cool and hiding in the shadows beneath the huge canopy of the mighty Oak tree Barry was lying under.","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"513eee21-7209-40fa-bf9b-40bfb83c74ad","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"9cda03c8-d755-42a8-aa37-1cebaeb382a6","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"Unbeknownst to Barry, across the Wilderwhim Woods, two very different adventures were unfolding at the very same time.\n\nOn one side of the forest was Elliot Stringfellow \u2014 a nine year old boy who loved nature, animals and his ukulele. He always carried two things: a little tree frog in the front pocket of his T-shirt and a ukulele strapped across his back.","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"1024b017-4830-4050-ae72-3c044be36679","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"d700fe5f-92b5-4be4-bf09-f8a8176f8037","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"Elliot zigged\u2026then zagged\u2026then zigged again.\n\n\"Wait! Come back!\" He laughed, as his little green frog leapt right out of his pocket and headed toward the river. Elliot's ukulele bounced on his back as he ran, his red high top tennis shoes tapping quickly along the path. It was their very own game of leap frog!","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"d993eb0f-15eb-467d-bf36-ae96423a5dab","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"5dbc472c-7775-4dc3-8376-9eac9cf22357","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"At the very same time, on the other side of Wilderwhim Woods, little Miss Juniper Bloom was tiptoeing through the grass, her net held high in both hands. She was following a monarch butterfly that zigzagged through the air.\n\nShe wore her favorite denim overalls and Birkenstocks, with a bright flower always tucked just above her ear.","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"25da85dc-a631-43c3-8d3d-3c943a31c1b5","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"07b344b2-130c-4de3-b436-05d198dfaa96","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"As Juniper followed and Elliot chased \u2014 without noticing, they both arrived at the very same spot at the exact same time!\n\nRight beside a BEAR!\n\nElliot skidded to a stop on one side. Juniper paused, lowering her net on the other. They both stared at the bear lying between them.","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"8c2299c1-c8ef-4bc6-8ba0-7f4ac584bf18","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"8b4cd391-8acb-410a-8f89-1055e5fc1815","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"Then Elliot looked up. Juniper looked up. Their eyes met and before either of them said a word, they smiled.\n\nBecause in the Wilderwhim Woods, that's how most good stories begin.","fontSize":24,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"dcb931e6-654b-46b6-98db-164310d7bcd7","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"9c78656f-81b3-45c3-9127-6babd58557a8","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"Barry stretched, blinked twice, and sat right up.\n\n\"Well hello there!\" Barry said with a warm smile.\n\n\"Hello! What's your name?\"\n\nBarry puffed his chest. \"Barry Goodwon.\"\n\nJuniper smiled. \"Well, nice to meet you. How are you today?\"\n\nBarry's eyes twinkled. \"Terrific.\"","fontSize":22,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"11afbd6b-f42a-4b96-a6b4-7bb2b812964b","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"9bd31a83-44ff-4e81-b646-3f1f46ecf561","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"\"So\u2026 what should we do now?\"\n\nBarry scratched his chin. \"In Wilderwhim Woods, the best thing to do is see who might need a little help\u2026 or a little hello.\"\n\nElliott's eyes lit up. \"A little hello sounds easy.\"\n\nJuniper nodded. \"And friendly.\"","fontSize":22,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"094badce-bbde-4f1c-9461-58799cb20484","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"02d95d33-2270-4ecd-b425-cad120772ce6","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"From the bushes came a sudden rustle. Two squirrels popped out at once.\n\n\"RADAR!\" said the first, standing tall with a paw to his ear.\n\"SONAR!\" said the second, spinning in a tiny circle.\n\n\"We're picking something up,\" RADAR announced.\n\"\u2026New friends,\" they whispered together.","fontSize":22,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"123c00ad-6ef2-4db0-a90b-03f7b4b15fef","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"0b430f34-40ce-4b64-866c-d85183395080","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"RADAR squinted at Barry. \"Big bear. Smiling. Confirmed terrific energy.\"\n\nSONAR sniffed the air. \"Also\u2026 calm approaching.\"\n\nBarry tilted his head. \"Oh! That'll be Doc.\"\n\nFrom the trail came a soft hop\u2026ouch\u2026hop\u2026ouch\u2026 Harry Hopwell appeared, limping carefully.\n\n\"How are you today, Harry?\"\nHarry sighed. \"Well, not terrific.\"","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"a39e6d16-75d0-45f9-9044-415bf3559710","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"1e53bc78-54d2-4cc0-b3ed-822b52a0dc23","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"Doc, the calm and caring tortoise, opened his shell just like a doctor opening his medical bag.\n\n\"Oh,\" Doc said calmly. \"You are very lucky! It's just a rabbit's foot! I will wrap it and you will be just fine.\"\n\nRadar gasped. \"Picking up relief!\"\nSonar nodded. \"Confirmed. Relief.\"\n\nHarry smiled. Barry smiled too. \"Terrific.\"","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"4e399c02-a89a-41da-ab94-887c44169a10","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"ff74429b-97f5-447a-a11d-db0bc3390487","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"PLOP! Elliot's pocket frog jumped out and zipped down the trail. Everyone followed \u2014 walking, hopping and laughing through the woods.\n\nThey were following CAKE CRUMBS!\n\nThe trail opened to a sunny clearing. Balloons bobbed happily. A banner fluttered high between the trees.\n\nHAPPY BIRTHDAY BARRY!\nYou are TERRIFIC!","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"efe93959-6400-4578-90fd-e39a28713809","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"c0c9cd8f-0955-4ff9-bbc5-dae6880b865b","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"Radar whispered. \"Birthday cake.\"\nSonar licked his lips. \"Confirmed.\"\n\nTella Mae Somptin stepped forward. \"My dear friends, old friends and new \u2014 kindness and charm are powerful things. They create happiness and joy.\"\n\nBarry's eyes reflected the joy around him.","fontSize":22,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"bec4ae58-d001-4001-8068-120c8faf918a","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"055a1583-50f5-4f21-9c6e-b4af80445043","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"From beneath the tall blades of grass, a shiny green snake with a party hat peeked out. It was Sssylvia Hissabell.\n\n\"Oh dear. I didn't think anyone would see me.\"\n\nBarry stepped closer, gentle as ever. \"Well hello there. How are you today?\"\n\nSssylvia hesitated. \"Well, not terrific. Not everyone cares for snakes. I thought it might be better if I stayed tucked away.\"","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"fb79eb7e-2b55-41e5-a0ed-a03ac3b677fc","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"c7e93c87-5434-4e57-9508-19b0e882b85e","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"Juniper knelt down. \"That doesn't sound very fair.\"\n\nBarry smiled his biggest smile. \"In Wilderwhim Woods, everyone belongs.\"\n\nSssylvia's eyes widened. \"Even me?\"\n\n\"Especially you,\" Barry said. \"Because kindness is terrific.\"\n\nSlowly, Sssylvia slid closer to the table. There was room for one more friend.","fontSize":22,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"ba1218a4-73d2-4c92-9b4d-c2865fc9a230","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"d76a1194-f44b-46ff-ac8d-1df93022c0c8","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"Down glided Tella Mae Somptin, her warm tawny feathers catching the light. She wore large, framed glasses and carried a well-loved journal.\n\n\"In Wilderwhim Woods, we learn something important again and again. The power of kindness \u2014 and the charm of caring for one another \u2014 creates happiness and joy.\"\n\nRadar leaned toward Sonar. \"Confirmed\u2026wise owl moment.\"","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"68f70bfd-99a1-45c3-a5c8-9376fabf7afc","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false},{"id":"1170638e-3adf-4852-aa09-ce9e45657664","layoutId":"picture-bottom","text":"Tella Mae closed her journal. \"Today, we celebrate not just a birthday\u2026 but the way being terrific means being kind.\"\n\nBarry scratched his chin, eyes shining. \"Well,\" he said happily, \"I'd say that's\u2026 Terrific!\"\n\nAnd in the Wilderwhim Woods, everyone agreed that being terrific meant being kind.\n\nTo be continued\u2026\u2026.","fontSize":22,"fontFamily":"Georgia, serif","textColor":"#1a1a2e","textAlign":"left","textZone":{"x":8,"y":8,"w":84,"h":36},"images":[{"id":"b923f35a-bf99-46c9-88e9-aa936c346e58","src":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","x":8,"y":50,"w":84,"h":44,"locked":false,"zIndex":1,"placeholder":false}],"overlays":[],"bgColor":"#ffffff","isTitlePage":false}],"currentPageIdx":0};
export default BARRY_BOOK;
